  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Combine your <strong>baharat</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a bowl with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then cut your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into strips</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1650385860984-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1650385860984-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1650385860984-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1650385860984-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1650385860984-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chicken strips</strong> to the bowl, give everything a good mix up and thread the <strong>chicken strips </strong>evenly onto each <strong>skewer </strong>and transfer to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Combine 3/4 of your <strong>lamb mince</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>mint sauce</strong> in a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Divide and shape the <strong>lamb mixture</strong> into 1 long, flat sausage per person, then add to the baking tray[s] – these are your <strong>minted</strong> <strong>lamb kebabs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1650385868709-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1650385868709-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1650385868709-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
